    "response": "To compute the **sample standard deviation** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{25, 10, 0, 9, -1, -14, -21\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the mean (average) of the data set\n\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 + (-1) + (-14) + (-21)}{7}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 - 1 - 14 - 21}{7}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 - 1 - 14 - 21}{7} = \\frac{10}{7} \\approx 1.4286\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Subtract the mean from each data point and square the result\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(25 - 1.4286)^2 &= 23.5714^2 \\approx 555.43 \\\\\n(10 - 1.4286)^2 &= 8.5714^2 \\approx 73.48 \\\\\n(0 - 1.4286)^2 &= (-1.4286)^2 \\approx 2.04 \\\\\n(9 - 1.4286)^2 &= 7.5714^2 \\approx 57.33 \\\\\n(-1 - 1.4286)^2 &= (-2.4286)^2 \\approx 5.89 \\\\\n(-14 - 1.4286)^2 &= (-15.4286)^2 \\approx 238.03 \\\\\n(-21 - 1.4286)^2 &= (-22.4286)^2 \\approx 502.84 \\\\\n\\end{align*}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Sum the squared differences\n\n$$\n555.43 + 73.48 + 2.04 + 57.33 + 5.89 + 238.03 + 502.84 \\approx"
